The paper describes a system for visualizing and analyzing research topics, which involves gathering data from Google Scholar academic research profiles. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the organization, storage, retrieval, and dissemination of information. Additionally, the paper involves the use of data visualization techniques, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of map overlays to visualize the strengths and weaknesses of different academic institutions, which could place it in the Software Development (cs.SD) or Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories, depending on the specific focus of the analysis.
